---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
import "../../styles/case-base.css";   

const title = "Case Study: Visual explorations";
---
<Base title={title} noWrap={false} hideFooter={false}>
  <header class="case-hero">
    <h1>Graphic Design</h1>
    <p class="meta">Visual Communication • Illustration • Art Direction • 2013–2025</p>
    <p class="lede">
      My background in fine arts (BA, Estonian Academy of Arts) has deeply shaped how I approach design — 
      composition, rhythm, and emotion are as important to me as structure, usability, and clarity. 
      My graphic design work moves across mediums: from posters and campaigns to brand identity and editorial layouts. 
      I combine visual storytelling and typographic precision to create memorable, functional, and human-centered design.
    </p>
  </header>

  <article class="container-narrow doc-grid tokens-case">
    <div class="doc-main">
      
      <!-- Featured visual -->
      <section class="hero-vertical" aria-label="Featured previews">
        <button class="shot-tile ar-21x9"
          data-full="/images/visual/purgid-up.png"
          data-title="Poster Design"
          data-cap="<p><strong>Exploring contrast and composition.</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>Balancing type and illustration to communicate emotion.</li>
            <li>Experimentation with hierarchy and asymmetry.</li>
            <li>Combining analog texture with digital precision.</li>
          </ul>">
          <img loading="lazy" src="/images/visual/purgid-up.png" alt="Poster design composition study">
        </button>
      </section>
      
      <section id="s-context">
        <h2>Context & Purpose</h2>
        <p>
          Graphic design has been at the intersection of my artistic and analytical interests. 
          My education in fine arts gave me a foundation in form, color, and composition, 
          while my work in UX/UI taught me to balance expression with structure. 
          These projects explore how emotion and function can coexist in design — 
          whether through campaigns, posters, or digital materials.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section id="s-approach">
        <h2>Approach</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Research-driven visual storytelling — understanding the subject before defining the aesthetic.</li>
          <li>Using typography, color, and imagery to convey rhythm and meaning.</li>
          <li>Combining traditional illustration methods with vector graphics and digital layout tools.</li>
          <li>Designing compositions that guide attention and evoke mood, while maintaining functional clarity.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section id="s-outcomes">
        <h2>Outcomes</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Developed a cohesive visual voice across multiple projects and media.</li>
          <li>Created visual systems that balance artistic expression with communication goals.</li>
          <li>Refined understanding of how emotional tone supports brand and interface experiences.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section id="s-role">
        <h2>My Role</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Concept creation and art direction from sketch to final layout.</li>
          <li>Illustration, typography, and composition for campaign and identity projects.</li>
          <li>Experimentation with analog and digital workflows for unique textures and depth.</li>
          <li>Bridging traditional visual design with UX principles and system thinking.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <p class="flex-col">
        <a class="btn link-btn" href="/case-studies/nav-system">
          <span class="btn-label">Check a demo of unified navigation menu</span>
          <i class="ri-arrow-right-line"></i>
        </a>
        <a class="btn link-btn" href="/case-studies/dash-case">
            <span class="btn-label">Dashboards and app interfaces</span>
          <i class="ri-arrow-right-line"></i>
        </a>
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- RIGHT: Visual panels / works ------------------------------->
    <aside class="doc-aside feature-card">
      <nav class="shots-grid" aria-label="Visual gallery">
        <button class="shot-tile"
          data-full="/images/visual/typesetter2.png"
          data-title="Typography Study"
          data-cap="<p>Balancing hierarchy and visual rhythm.</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Exploring typographic relationships through composition.</li>
            <li>Using grid and space to emphasize message and tone.</li>
          </ul>">
          <img src="/images/visual/typesetter2.png" alt="Typography composition study">
        </button>

